Russian militants in Donbass again violated Minsk agreements
Two soldiers were injured and injured.

01 Nov 2019, 08:31

Armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries have violated the ceasefire regime 15 times over the past October 31, 15 times. In particular, the 82 mm banned mortar agreements were used, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns, as well as other small arms and BMPs.
In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "EAST" the enemy made 7 shells:
near Novogrigorovka and Nevelsky - machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
nearby Kamenka - hand-held anti-tank grenade launchers and small arms;
three times in the water district of the Azov region - with armaments BMP-1, small arms and grenade launchers of different systems;
near Lebedinsky - from large-caliber machine guns.
In the area of responsibility of tactical group "NORTH" the enemy carried out 8 shelling:
near Svitlodarsk - automatic grenade launchers;
twice near Lugansk - from large-caliber machine guns and machine-gun anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Novolugansk - automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Crimean - from 82 mm mortars, automatic grenade launchers and large machine guns;
nearby the South - with anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near the Trinity - from large-caliber machine guns;
near Novotoshkivsky - 82 mm mortars.
On Thursday, a wounded soldier of the Allied Forces, another suffered a combat injury.
From the beginning of this day, armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries, in the area of responsibility of the operational-tactical group "PIVNICH", fired at our positions near Lugansk with RPGs, large machine guns and other small arms.
On the morning of October 29, Foreign Minister Vadim Prystayko announced the start of the deployment of forces and assets near Zolotoy in Luhansk region. At the headquarters of the OOS, this information was initially denied, but later confirmed that the deployment of troops began at 12:00 q specified that it would last three days.
Breeding in Zolotoy, Stanitsa Lugansk (Lugansk region) and Petrovsky (Donetsk region) was repeatedly coordinated in Minsk, but failed during the implementation attempt. In the summer of this year, troops deployed in the area of Luhansk Stanytsy, after which, at a meeting on October 1, the Trilateral Contact Group agreed to breach two more sections on the Donbass collision line.
Detachment of Ukrainian troops from the demarcation line is one of the conditions for the Kremlin to hold a Normandy format summit. At the same time, they refused to guarantee a mirror removal of the occupying troops in the Kremlin.
Veterans and volunteers of the Russo-Ukrainian war, as well as civilians of the front-line settlements, opposed the expulsion of the Ukrainian military. The former consider divorce a capitulation in the war with Russia, while others fear the massacre of fighters after the departure of the Ukrainian military from their positions.
For more information on the implementation of Zelensky's plan for the deployment of troops in the Donbass and its consequences, see Yuri Butusov's article "The Zelensky War: Can Putin be Dismissed by Divorce?" in the "Mirror of the Week. Ukraine" weekly.
